         <abstract>
            <p>This paper attempts to present a unified treatment of the classical orthogonal polynomials, viz. Jacobi, Laguerre and Hermite polynomials, and their generalizations introduced from time to time. The results obtained here include a number of linear, bilinear and bilateral generating functions and operational formulas for the polynomials $\{T_n^{(\alpha, \beta)}(x, a, b, c, d, p, r) \mid n = 0, 1, 2,\cdots\}$, defined by Eq. (3) below.</p>
          </abstract>
